The paper proposes a new physical layer technique for enhancing the security of cooperative relay communications, which involves modifying the decoded message at the relay according to the unique channel state between the relay and the destination. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories, as it presents a practical method for securely sharing the modification rule between the legitimate partners and analyzes the secrecy outage probability in a quasi-static fading channel.
